---
const groups = [
  {
    category: 'Practical',
    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'What is the time commitment?',
        a: 'Time commitment varies by course, but most Founding Faculty invest a small number of dedicated days across the design and filming process, planned entirely around your schedule.',
      },
      {
        q: 'How much preparation is required?',
        a: 'We handle curriculum structuring, scripting support, and logistics. You bring the clinical expertise. Preparation is guided closely by our educational design team so it never falls entirely on you.',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Production',
    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'What does filming involve?',
        a: 'Filming is professionally produced, either at a studio or a location that suits you. Sessions are structured, unhurried, and designed to capture your teaching at its best.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Will I need to use a teleprompter?',
        a: 'A teleprompter is available if useful, but it is entirely optional. Many Founding Faculty prefer to teach conversationally from a structured outline.',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Travel',
    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'Is travel required?',
        a: 'Only if filming takes place away from your own location, and only by mutual agreement. Remote and hybrid production formats are also possible.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Is accommodation arranged?',
        a: 'Yes. Where travel is required, accommodation and related logistics are arranged and covered as part of the collaboration.',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Agreement',
    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'What is the revenue model?',
        a: 'Revenue terms are discussed individually and confirmed in writing before any production begins, so expectations are clear from the outset.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Who owns the intellectual property?',
        a: 'IP arrangements are agreed in advance and documented formally. We are glad to walk through the specific terms during our conversation.',
      },
      {
        q: 'How are course updates handled?',
        a: 'Clinical knowledge evolves, and course material is reviewed periodically. Updates are coordinated with you rather than made unilaterally.',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Academic Review',
    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'Do I have final review over the material?',
        a: 'Yes. Nothing bearing your name is published without your explicit approval at the faculty review stage.',
      },
      {
        q: 'What support is provided throughout?',
        a: 'A dedicated educational design and production team supports you from first conversation through to launch and beyond.',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    category: 'Long-term',
    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'Is this a long-term collaboration?',
        a: 'Founding Faculty status is intended as an ongoing academic relationship, not a one-off engagement.',
      },
      {
        q: 'Is AI used anywhere in the process?',
        a: 'AI tools may assist with production efficiency, such as editing support, but all clinical content and final decisions rest with you and our academic team.',
      },
      {
        q: 'What is meant by educational design?',
        a: 'Educational design is the discipline of translating clinical expertise into a structured, deliberately sequenced learning experience, applied by our team throughout the process.',
      },
    ],
  },
];
---
<section class="bg-paper">
  <div class="container-prose py-14 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-10 md:mb-12">
      <div class="eyebrow mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</div>
      <div class="rule-gold"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-10 md:space-y-12">
      {groups.map((g) => (
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow text-champagne mb-2">{g.category}</div>
          <div class="divide-y divide-platinum-soft border-t border-platinum-soft">
            {g.faqs.map((f) => (
              <details class="group py-6">
                <summary class="ff-faq-summary flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-6 font-serif text-lg md:text-xl text-navy-deep rounded-sm">
                  <span>{f.q}</span>
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="h-3.5 w-3.5 shrink-0 text-champagne transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d="M8 1v14M1 8h14" />
                  </svg>
                </summary>
                <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-graphite leading-relaxed">{f.a}</p>
              </details>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<style>
  .ff-faq-summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }
  .ff-faq-summary:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-champagne);
    outline-offset: 6px;
  }
</style>
